    "summary": "Dr. Benson A. Mulemi is an associate professor of Medical Anthropology and Senior Research fellow in Social Sciences. He is a Research Associate  at the Centre for the Advancement of Scholarship, Faculty of Humanities, University of Pretoria. He is also a 2023 Virtual Fellow in the African Ecologies  research Programme of the Leeds Centre for African Studies/ Leeds Arts and Humanities Research Institute, University of Leeds . Dr. Mulemi worked at the Catholic University of Eastern Africa (CUEA) From January 1999 to May 2021. He was the Acting Deputy Vice Chancellor--Research, Innovation &Partnerships at CUEA in 2018-2019. He was the Research coordinator in the Directorate of Research and Graduate Training from 2016  to 2019 and Acting Director of the Directorate of Research and Innovation ad Graduate Training;  2017-2019. He worked on several projects as a research fellow, lecturer and university supervisor at CUEA,  visiting lecturer at the Institute of Anthropology, Gender & African Studies; University of Nairobi, Institute for Peace Studies & International Relations (Hekima College), Christ the Teacher Institute for Education, Theological Center for Religious; Tangaza college and the Jesuit School of Theology; Hekima University college in Nairobi. His current research focus on Cancer Narratives in Kenya, and Albinism, Witchcraft, superstitions in and lived experiences of People with Albinism in East Africa (With the first phase of fieldwork in Mwanza, Dar es salaam and Mtwara regions in Tanzania); Ethnography of Cancer Care in Kenya. He was awarded the British Academy of Humanities and Social Sciences visiting scholar grant; tenable at the Centre of African Studies (CAS) and Wolfson College; University of Cambridge, September- December 2011. He was also a Visiting Research Fellow at the University of  Cambridge, CAS during the 2014-2015 award period, supported by the A.G. Leventis Foundation. He is a visiting Professor in the Masters of Medical Anthropology Proramme in the Department of Mental Health, Faculty of Medicine, Gulu University, Uganda.",
